<para>Any actions which modify state should inhert from <link linkend="_namespace_luthetus_1_1_text_editor_1_1_razor_lib_1_1_text_editors_1_1_states_1a6a2ec19dac2b03c9354d04b880bfe184">TextEditorAuthenticatedAction</link>.<?linebreak?> <?linebreak?> Doing this permits state modifications to be concurrency safe. They will be enqueued using ITextEditorService.EnqueueEdit(Func&lt;ITextEditorEditContext, Task&gt;).<?linebreak?> <?linebreak?> When it is a specific edit&apos;s turn to perform their modification, all state will be provided by the <link linkend="_interface_luthetus_1_1_text_editor_1_1_razor_lib_1_1_i_text_editor_service">ITextEditorService</link>.<?linebreak?> <?linebreak?> Therefore no state modification can be done without the <link linkend="_class_luthetus_1_1_text_editor_1_1_razor_lib_1_1_text_editor_service_1ab734191e9f88c71d3763f87bf382b014">TextEditorService.AuthenticatedActionKey</link>.<?linebreak?> <?linebreak?> The <link linkend="_class_luthetus_1_1_text_editor_1_1_razor_lib_1_1_text_editor_service_1ab734191e9f88c71d3763f87bf382b014">TextEditorService.AuthenticatedActionKey</link> is public, so one could subvert this. But, it shouldn&apos;t be subverted, the key is public in order to provide clarity in how the &quot;authentication&quot; is being done.<?linebreak?> <?linebreak?> TODO: Learn more about SynchronizationContext. </para>
